<div style="text-align:center; padding: 3rem 0 1rem;">
  <h1 style="color: var(--accent); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
    Turtle Logo
  </h1>
  <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #ccc; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    A Logo interpreter for kids &mdash; learn to draw with code!
  </p>
  <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
    <a href="/play/" style="background: var(--accent-dim); color: #fff; padding: 0.6rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 6px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 1rem; text-decoration: none;">
      Play Now
    </a>
    <a href="/book/" style="background: var(--border); color: #fff; padding: 0.6rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 6px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 1rem; text-decoration: none;">
      Read the Turtle Book
    </a>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="max-width: 600px; margin: 2rem auto; text-align: center;">
  <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    Type commands. The turtle moves and draws.<br>
    <strong>FD 100</strong> — go forward.<br>
    <strong>RT 90</strong> — turn right.<br>
    <strong>REPEAT 4 [FD 80 RT 90]</strong> — draw a square!
  </p>

  <p style="color: #888; font-size: 0.9rem;">
    Turtle Logo runs entirely in your browser. No installation needed.<br>
    Inspired by MSX Logo.
  </p>
</div>
